# Docs Hub

This `docs/` folder contains all thesis writing material and supporting documents.

## Roles / Where to look

### 1) Thesis writing (LaTeX template)

- Main template folder: `docs/BT/CTU_FEL_THESIS/`
- Entry file (compile this): `docs/BT/CTU_FEL_THESIS/thesis-final.tex`
- Template class (title pages + layout): `docs/BT/CTU_FEL_THESIS/phdthesis.cls`
- Chapters live in: `docs/BT/CTU_FEL_THESIS/chapters/`

Read first:
- `docs/BT/CTU_FEL_THESIS/README.md`

### 2) Thesis planning (what to write)

- Planning hub: `docs/BT/thesis_doc/`
	- Index: `docs/BT/thesis_doc/README.md`
	- Chinese guide (Overleaf + writing workflow): `docs/BT/thesis_doc/README.zh-CN.md`

### 3) Faculty rules / admin paperwork

- Requirements summary: `docs/BT/Bachelor_project_Rules.md`
- Original PDF: `docs/BT/Bachelor_project_Rules.pdf`

### 4) Proposal / assignment documents

- Proposal: `docs/BT/BT_WeizeYUAN_proposal_v0.docx`
- Proposal (Markdown): `docs/BT/BT_WeizeYUAN_proposal_v0.md`
- Assignment-related files: see the rest of `docs/BT/`

## Build (local)

The LaTeX template uses LuaLaTeX + biblatex/biber.

From `docs/BT/CTU_FEL_THESIS/`:

```bash
lualatex thesis-final.tex
biber thesis-final
lualatex thesis-final.tex
lualatex thesis-final.tex
```

### Draft vs print layout

By default, the template compiles in **draft-friendly oneside** mode (no left/right margin swapping).

For final double-sided printing with binding margins, change the first line of `thesis-final.tex` to:

```tex
\documentclass[print]{phdthesis}
```

### Clean

If you use `latexmk`:

```bash
latexmk -c   # keep PDF
latexmk -C   # remove PDF too
```

Or manual clean:

```bash
rm -f *.aux *.bbl *.bcf *.blg *.run.xml *.toc *.lof *.lot *.out *.log \
	*.fls *.fdb_latexmk *.synctex.gz
```
